Part 1 – Greedy Strategies
--------------------------------------------------------

All three greedy strategies share the same selection loop. They differ only in sort order.

GREEDY_SELECT(experiments sorted by some criterion, weightLimit):
    chosen       ← empty list
    totalWeight  ← 0
    totalRating  ← 0

    FOR each experiment e in sorted order:
        IF totalWeight + e.weight ≤ weightLimit:
            ADD e to chosen
            totalWeight ← totalWeight + e.weight
            totalRating ← totalRating + e.rating
        // Otherwise skip — greedy never revisits

    RETURN Solution(chosen, totalWeight, totalRating)

---

GREEDY_HIGHEST_RATING(experiments, weightLimit):
    sorted ← experiments sorted by rating DESCENDING
    RETURN GREEDY_SELECT(sorted, weightLimit)

GREEDY_LIGHTEST_FIRST(experiments, weightLimit):
    sorted ← experiments sorted by weight ASCENDING
    RETURN GREEDY_SELECT(sorted, weightLimit)

GREEDY_BEST_RATIO(experiments, weightLimit):
    sorted ← experiments sorted by (rating / weight) DESCENDING
    RETURN GREEDY_SELECT(sorted, weightLimit)




Part 2 – Brute Force Exhaustive Search
--------------------------------------------------------

BRUTE_FORCE(experiments, weightLimit):
    validSolutions ← empty list
    BRUTE_FORCE_RECURSIVE(experiments, 0, empty list, weightLimit, validSolutions)
    SORT validSolutions by totalRating DESCENDING
    RETURN first 3 elements of validSolutions   // index 0 = optimal


BRUTE_FORCE_RECURSIVE(experiments, index, currentSubset, weightLimit, validSolutions):

    // Base case: every experiment has been considered
    IF index == length of experiments:
        totalWeight ← sum of weights in currentSubset
        totalRating ← sum of ratings in currentSubset
        IF totalWeight ≤ weightLimit AND currentSubset is not empty:
            ADD Solution(currentSubset, totalWeight, totalRating) to validSolutions
        RETURN

    // Option A: skip experiment at current index
    BRUTE_FORCE_RECURSIVE(experiments, index + 1, currentSubset, weightLimit, validSolutions)

    // Option B: include experiment at current index
    ADD experiments[index] to currentSubset
    BRUTE_FORCE_RECURSIVE(experiments, index + 1, currentSubset, weightLimit, validSolutions)
    REMOVE experiments[index] from currentSubset  // backtrack



