Part 4 – Dynamic Programming (extra credit)
--------------------------------------------------------

DYNAMIC_PROGRAMMING(experiments, weightLimit):
    n      ← length of experiments
    dp     ← 2D table of size (n+1) × (weightLimit+1), all zeros

    // dp[i][w] = best rating using first i experiments with capacity w

    // Base cases: row 0 and column 0 are already 0

    FOR i FROM 1 TO n:
        exp ← experiments[i - 1]
        FOR w FROM 0 TO weightLimit:

            // Option A: skip experiment i
            dp[i][w] ← dp[i-1][w]

            // Option B: include experiment i (only if it fits)
            IF exp.weight ≤ w:
                withItem ← dp[i-1][w - exp.weight] + exp.rating
                IF withItem > dp[i][w]:
                    dp[i][w] ← withItem

    // optimalRating ← dp[n][weightLimit]

    // Traceback to find which experiments were chosen
    chosen ← TRACEBACK(dp, experiments, weightLimit)

    RETURN Solution(chosen, sum of weights in chosen, optimalRating)


TRACEBACK(dp, experiments, weightLimit):
    chosen ← empty list
    w      ← weightLimit

    FOR i FROM n DOWN TO 1:
        IF dp[i][w] ≠ dp[i-1][w]:          // experiment i included
            ADD experiments[i-1] to front of chosen
            w ← w - experiments[i-1].weight // reduce remaining capacity

    RETURN chosen



Complexity Summary
--------------------------------------------------------


| Algorithm | Time Complexity | Space Complexity | Finds Optimal? |
|-----------|-----------------|------------------|----------------|
| Greedy (any) | O(n log n) | O(n) | Not guaranteed |
| Brute Force | O(2ⁿ × n) | O(2ⁿ) | Yes |
| Dynamic Programming | O(n × W) | O(n × W) | Yes |


